    "In panel data with a matrix structure that denotes student click behaviors, LSTM is excellent for learning the features.",
    "Table 8, shows a summary of all studies that used hybrid DL merged with either ML or Ensemble Learning techniques.",
    "Botelho et al (2019) examined high and low representations of unproductive persistence, which are described as student \"stopout\" and \"wheel spinning\" using a transfer learning include DL and conventional modeling methodologies.",
    "The study used LSTM, Decision Tree, and Logistic Regression to construct early detectors of these behaviors.",
    "Models created to identify both withinand across-assignment stopouts and wheel spinning were found to be able to learn sets of attributes that generalize to predict the other."
